295
00:12:41,040 --> 00:12:44,840
you brought the Japanese in to frame Great-grandfather.

296
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:47,200
Just for a house,

297
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:50,240
you pushed Great-grandfather to a dead end.

298
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,800
That was a dead end!

299
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:06,120
How could you do such dirty things?

300
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:08,400
Are you even human?

301
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:10,240
Why waste your breath on them?

302
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:11,640
I'll smash you to death!

303
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:12,440
Put it down.

304
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:17,880
This is between him and me.

305
00:13:21,480 --> 00:13:22,760
Zhang Yunqi,

306
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:24,560
Li Shuyuan.

307
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:27,500
If anything happens to Great-grandfather,

308
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:29,000
you two

309
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:32,360
will pay with your lives.

310
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:41,200
Remember,

311
00:13:41,520 --> 00:13:44,400
my cleaver is more effective than my fists.

312
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:26,160
I didn't mean to kill Uncle.

313
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:34,040
Uncle,

314
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:39,720
I didn't mean to kill Uncle either.

315
00:15:56,760 --> 00:15:57,640
Old man,

316
00:15:58,000 --> 00:15:59,640
the Japanese are pressing hard.

317
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:00,760
You are old.

318
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:02,760
Confess early,

319
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:05,130
so we can complete our task, right?

320
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:12,160
I didn't write the flyers.

321
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:15,440
But I agree with their content.

322
00:16:18,320 --> 00:16:19,480
Young men,

323
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:22,240
I think you should take this flyer

324
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:23,520
home,

325
00:16:23,760 --> 00:16:26,160
and show it to your siblings and relatives

326
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:27,680
to let them read

327
00:16:28,040 --> 00:16:29,160
and think about it.

328
00:16:31,720 --> 00:16:32,480
Speak.

329
00:16:32,760 --> 00:16:34,820
Who taught you to write these flyers?

330
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:36,480
I don't need to be taught.

331
00:16:37,520 --> 00:16:39,640
These are my true feelings.

332
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:43,320
They are also the true feelings of every Chinese person,

333
00:16:43,320 --> 00:16:45,320
and yours too.

334
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:46,760
Am I right?

335
00:16:46,920 --> 00:16:47,720
Old geezer,

336
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:50,080
I don't want to make things difficult for you

337
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:51,210
because of your age.

338
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:52,800
Don't push your luck.

339
00:17:01,760 --> 00:17:02,960
My son

340
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:06,119
on the battlefield in Shanghai,

341
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:08,560
died a heroic death.

342
00:17:09,119 --> 00:17:11,250
Although I can't go to the frontlines,

343
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:14,240
can't I speak my mind?

344
00:17:14,440 --> 00:17:16,800
Don't I even dare to admit it?

345
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:18,520
By doing so,

346
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:21,480
I would let down my son who died in battle,

347
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:24,839
and his passionate blood.

348
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:33,720
Today,

349
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:37,360
I will tell you

350
00:17:37,560 --> 00:17:39,360
my true feelings properly.

351
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:41,720
I am a dying man.

352
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:44,360
You are all still young.

353
00:17:44,560 --> 00:17:45,560
China

354
00:17:46,080 --> 00:17:48,800
cannot perish in our hands.

355
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:50,080
Take him out

356
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:51,000
and torture him.

357
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:52,600
Facing a formidable enemy,

358
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:53,760
Let's see how tough you are.

359
00:17:53,760 --> 00:17:55,420
Raping, burning and killing,

360
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:57,320
and committing all kinds of evil.

361
00:17:57,960 --> 00:18:01,920
We should rise up and resist.

362
00:18:02,320 --> 00:18:03,600
So many young people

363
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:05,600
are stepping into the breach.

364
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:07,240
You should

365
00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:09,960
rush to the front

366
00:18:10,280 --> 00:18:12,480
to kill the enemy and serve the country.

367
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:24,720
Mrs. Zhang.

368
00:18:24,720 --> 00:18:25,280
Lawyer Wu.

369
00:18:25,280 --> 00:18:26,000
Over there.

370
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:30,440
Lawyer Wu.

371
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:32,400
The old gentleman has a strong backbone,

372
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:33,600
but he is at a disadvantage now.

373
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:34,800
He is really wronged.

374
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:35,640
I know.

375
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:37,200
But the Japanese military police

376
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:38,480
are keeping a very close eye on it now.

377
00:18:38,480 --> 00:18:40,480
The police station can't do anything either.

378
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:41,480
I think we must now

379
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:42,960
try our best

380
00:18:43,120 --> 00:18:44,360
to delay the police station.

381
00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:45,160
We can't let the old man

382
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:47,820
be extradited to the Japanese military police.

383
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:49,600
If he really gets into the military police,

384
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:51,520
almost no one can come back alive.

385
00:18:54,680 --> 00:18:55,400
Mrs. Zhang.

386
00:18:55,840 --> 00:18:57,680
I think the most effective way now

387
00:18:57,680 --> 00:18:59,560
is to start with the Japanese military police

388
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:00,400
and find a way.

389
00:19:00,680 --> 00:19:01,960
As long as they relent,

390
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:03,480
the Petain police station

391
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:04,640
will be easier to talk to.

392
00:19:04,640 --> 00:19:06,370
The Japanese military police.

393
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:07,000
This...

394
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,530
How do we grease the wheels?

395
00:19:09,280 --> 00:19:10,480
I will do my best

396
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:12,360
to figure something out.

397
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:17,000
Can I go in and see my father now?

398
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,160
I'm afraid not for the next couple of days.

399
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:19,400
But my father is all alone now.

400
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:20,240
Mrs. Zhang,

401
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:21,920
I'll negotiate with them again.

402
00:19:21,920 --> 00:19:23,320
You should go back first.

403
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:24,440
I will let you know tomorrow

404
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:25,600
if there is any news.

405
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:27,320
Thank you, Mr. Wu.

406
00:19:27,320 --> 00:19:28,400
Thank you, Mr. Wu.

407
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:29,720
Thank you.

408
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:40,930
Let's go, Madam.

409
00:19:41,520 --> 00:19:42,320
Let's go back.

410
00:19:43,760 --> 00:19:44,560
Wanfu,

411
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:48,340
go back to the restaurant.

412
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,000
No.

413
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:50,240
Go back yourself.

414
00:19:50,240 --> 00:19:51,040
What if that bastard Zhang Yunqi

415
00:19:51,040 --> 00:19:52,040
acts crazy again?

416
00:19:52,720 --> 00:19:53,120
If he acts crazy again,

417
00:19:53,120 --> 00:19:54,280
I will beat him to death today.

418
00:19:54,280 --> 00:19:55,840
This is our family matter.

419
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:57,300
I'll handle it.

420
00:19:57,440 --> 00:19:59,000
Don't get involved anymore.

421
00:19:59,000 --> 00:19:59,280
I...

422
00:19:59,280 --> 00:20:00,010
Don't worry.

423
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:02,170
I won't do anything stupid.

424
00:20:02,360 --> 00:20:03,080
Madam,

425
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:04,400
go back.

426
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:28,840
Be gentle.

427
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:36,600
Is your neck okay?

428
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:38,920
Making do like this won't work.

429
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:41,240
You need to see a doctor tomorrow.

430
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:42,400
I'm fine.

431
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:43,680
Don't worry about me.

432
00:21:44,400 --> 00:21:46,200
We'll talk about my injury tomorrow.

433
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:47,920
Come, let's change the cotton. Come.

434
00:21:47,920 --> 00:21:48,920
I won't change it.

435
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:50,200
I won't change it. No.

436
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:50,880
It hurts.

437
00:22:05,560 --> 00:22:06,200
Come here.

438
00:22:08,960 --> 00:22:09,680
Come here.

439
00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:11,040
I won't hit you.

440
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:13,880
Come here.

441
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:37,200
Where is the book?

442
00:22:39,840 --> 00:22:40,600
What book?

443
00:22:41,280 --> 00:22:42,600
'Lushan Records'.

444
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:48,500
I gave it to Fujita.

445
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:50,640
You gave it to Fujita?

446
00:22:50,960 --> 00:22:52,160
Uncle beat Fujita.

447
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:53,120
I was desperate at the time,

448
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:54,760
so I gave the book to Fujita.

449
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:57,600
You gave it today?

450
00:23:00,360 --> 00:23:01,280
You're lying.

451
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:01,960
I'm not.

452
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:03,320
Only Grandpa and I

453
00:23:03,320 --> 00:23:04,320
know where this book is.

454
00:23:04,320 --> 00:23:07,380
Grandpa wouldn't let you give the book to the Japanese.

455
00:23:08,200 --> 00:23:09,400
When did you steal it?

456
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:12,680
A few days ago.

457
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:15,810
Sister-in-law.

458
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:17,260
Don't be angry yet.

459
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:19,290
Listen to me tell you the truth.

460
00:23:23,960 --> 00:23:25,120
Actually, the family's

461
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:26,720
stocks and bonds

462
00:23:26,920 --> 00:23:29,280
were all bought with loan shark money.

463
00:23:29,840 --> 00:23:31,520
Before this, renting out the house

464
00:23:31,520 --> 00:23:33,960
allowed me to use the rent to pay the loan shark.

465
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:35,840
They demand repayment on specific dates.

466
00:23:35,840 --> 00:23:37,000
If I can't pay the money,

467
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:37,880
they said

468
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:40,220
they'll throw me into the Huangpu River.

469
00:23:41,040 --> 00:23:42,840
But when you and Uncle came back,

470
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:45,600
you wanted to keep the rent collection rights to yourself.

471
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:46,200
And

472
00:23:46,680 --> 00:23:48,800
then you went to Lawyer Wu

473
00:23:48,920 --> 00:23:50,180
to get the title deeds.

474
00:23:50,360 --> 00:23:51,080
Blocking me from both sides,

475
00:23:51,080 --> 00:23:53,760
leaving me no way out.

476
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:55,600
I really had no choice.

477
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:56,880
Where is the book?

478
00:23:56,880 --> 00:23:58,520
That brings me to the book.

479
00:23:58,520 --> 00:23:59,200
I...

480
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:02,400
That day, Shuyuan and I,

481
00:24:02,760 --> 00:24:04,400
while Uncle was taking a nap,

482
00:24:05,920 --> 00:24:07,960
stole this box up here.

483
00:24:08,760 --> 00:24:11,020
I thought the title deeds were in the box.

484
00:24:11,040 --> 00:24:12,160
I originally wanted

485
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:14,440
to change the name on the deeds to mine,

486
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:16,720
or simply destroy them.

487
00:24:17,400 --> 00:24:19,360
So that when collecting rent later,

488
00:24:19,360 --> 00:24:20,840
I'd be fully justified.

489
00:24:21,080 --> 00:24:22,120
Or at the very least,

490
00:24:22,120 --> 00:24:23,600
if we split the rent in half,

491
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:24,260
I could also

492
00:24:24,520 --> 00:24:26,040
pay off that loan shark.

493
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:28,330
Who would have thought,

494
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:29,440
when I opened the box,

495
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:31,280
there were just some broken stones inside,

496
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:33,280
and that rare book Uncle collected.

497
00:24:33,960 --> 00:24:35,600
I figured Uncle had a good eye,

498
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:38,040
so 'Records of Mount Lu' must be valuable.

499
00:24:38,280 --> 00:24:39,760
So I hid it.

500
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:42,400
I thought if I was ever in a pinch,

501
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:44,400
it might fetch a good price.

502
00:24:44,520 --> 00:24:46,880
And it turns out, I used it today.

503
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:48,680
I invited Fujita to dinner,

504
00:24:48,680 --> 00:24:50,400
and Uncle came in and beat him up.

505
00:24:50,400 --> 00:24:51,320
You know how the Japanese are.

506
00:24:51,320 --> 00:24:52,200
If he really got angry,

507
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:54,000
he would have wiped out our whole family.

508
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:55,080
I was so desperate in the moment,

509
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:56,800
that I gave 'Records of Mount Lu'

510
00:24:56,800 --> 00:24:58,960
to Fujita, the China expert.

511
00:24:59,800 --> 00:25:01,640
And his anger really subsided.

512
00:25:01,760 --> 00:25:02,240
You see,

513
00:25:02,360 --> 00:25:03,640
he didn't call the military police.

514
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:05,570
He only called the police station.

515
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:08,450
Sister-in-law,

516
00:25:09,080 --> 00:25:09,600
I really

517
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:11,800
haven't lied to you at all.

518
00:25:11,800 --> 00:25:13,080
If I lied a single word,

519
00:25:13,080 --> 00:25:15,000
may lightning strike me.

520
00:25:24,720 --> 00:25:25,720
Zhang Yunqi.

521
00:25:26,640 --> 00:25:28,770
Whether what you said is true or false,

522
00:25:29,240 --> 00:25:30,570
and what you did before,

523
00:25:30,600 --> 00:25:32,480
I can overlook for now.

524
00:25:32,840 --> 00:25:34,640
I just have one question for you.

525
00:25:35,160 --> 00:25:36,760
Is he your real uncle?

526
00:25:39,680 --> 00:25:40,960
Yes.

527
00:25:42,760 --> 00:25:43,760
Your real uncle

528
00:25:44,520 --> 00:25:47,050
is currently locked up in the police station.

529
00:25:47,560 --> 00:25:49,640
This is a matter of life and death.

530
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:51,320
I know.

531
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:53,320
You know that Japanese man.

532
00:25:53,800 --> 00:25:54,720
Go find him,

533
00:25:55,640 --> 00:25:56,880
pull some strings,

534
00:25:57,280 --> 00:25:58,600
and get him out.

535
00:25:59,920 --> 00:26:01,200
Zhang Yunqi.

536
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:04,640
If you have any shred of humanity left,

537
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:06,600
if you still have

538
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:08,600
a heart,

539
00:26:10,280 --> 00:26:10,880
You...

540
00:26:11,160 --> 00:26:12,760
you should know what to do.

541
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:19,760
Also,

542
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:21,480
downstairs,

543
00:26:22,120 --> 00:26:24,040
what I said when I slapped you,

544
00:26:24,280 --> 00:26:26,440
both of you better remember.

545
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:29,320
If anything happens to him,

546
00:26:29,720 --> 00:26:30,880
you two

547
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:33,200
will pay with your lives.

548
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:36,140
I'm not speaking out of anger.

549
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:06,720
How can I save Uncle?

550
00:27:09,120 --> 00:27:10,080
Get up first.

551
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:10,760
Come.

552
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:14,760
I have no way to save Uncle at all.

553
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:16,490
Forget about Uncle for now.

554
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:20,360
You can barely save yourself.

555
00:27:20,840 --> 00:27:22,320
They are the Japanese.

556
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:23,680
Can you just order them

557
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:24,880
around as you please?

558
00:27:26,080 --> 00:27:27,320
How can you deal with them

559
00:27:27,320 --> 00:27:28,440
when they turn hostile

560
00:27:28,440 --> 00:27:29,800
at any moment?

561
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:31,280
Those bastards.

562
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:32,200
When they lose their temper,

563
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:33,680
they can do any evil thing.

564
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:35,220
They have no humanity.

565
00:27:37,040 --> 00:27:38,300
Then what should we do?

566
00:27:51,760 --> 00:27:52,640
Take this.

567
00:27:54,680 --> 00:27:56,720
Let's just sell this house

568
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:58,120
and 'Lushan Ji'

569
00:27:58,440 --> 00:27:59,800
to Fujita.

570
00:28:00,160 --> 00:28:01,490
And we run away quickly.

571
00:28:01,880 --> 00:28:02,880
Not saving Uncle?

572
00:28:03,040 --> 00:28:04,560
Stop talking about Uncle.

573
00:28:04,880 --> 00:28:07,360
Haven't you had enough of that woman's ruthlessness?

574
00:28:07,360 --> 00:28:08,440
And that guy Meng.

575
00:28:08,840 --> 00:28:09,800
What did he say?

576
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:12,530
His knife is even better than his fist.

577
00:28:14,040 --> 00:28:15,640
If we stay here any longer,

578
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:18,160
we'll lose our lives for this house.

579
00:28:19,120 --> 00:28:20,120
Say something.

580
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:21,930
I'm waiting for your decision.

581
00:28:23,760 --> 00:28:24,480
Like this.

582
00:28:26,280 --> 00:28:27,010
Are you okay?

583
00:28:28,320 --> 00:28:29,360
See if this works.

584
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:28,120
Dachang was defeated.

585
00:30:28,120 --> 00:30:29,580
Sun Huaiyi's poor command

586
00:30:29,680 --> 00:30:32,880
made you take the blame as the fleeing general.

587
00:30:33,240 --> 00:30:34,360
But I believe you.

588
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:38,120
You are not a coward.

589
00:30:38,400 --> 00:30:40,080
You would definitely fight the Japs

590
00:30:40,080 --> 00:30:41,880
to the last man.

591
00:30:42,200 --> 00:30:43,800
You wanted to sacrifice yourself,

592
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:45,440
but God didn't let you die.

593
00:30:46,160 --> 00:30:47,420
You fell into my hands.

594
00:30:48,880 --> 00:30:50,540
Then I must fulfill your wish.

595
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:51,680
Can I live?

596
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:52,840
No.

597
00:30:58,520 --> 00:31:00,520
I'm not the Zhang Yunkui I used to be.

598
00:31:00,600 --> 00:31:02,560
And you're not the Pang Zhonghao you used to be.

599
00:31:02,560 --> 00:31:03,440
I was at Songhu.

600
00:31:04,040 --> 00:31:04,970
I was at Nanjing.

601
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:06,440
You know it in your heart.

602
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:08,700
I'm better at fighting the Japs than you.

603
00:31:08,960 --> 00:31:10,640
I can help you kill more Japs.

604
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:12,960
And you can lose fewer brothers.

605
00:31:13,400 --> 00:31:15,000
Are you negotiating with me?

606
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:16,880
I must get my revenge today.

607
00:31:17,600 --> 00:31:20,000
I'll whip you once for every brother I lost.

608
00:31:20,080 --> 00:31:21,410
I'll whip you to pieces!

609
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:22,280
Strip him!

610
00:31:58,960 --> 00:31:59,760
Fresh wounds.

611
00:32:00,400 --> 00:32:01,280
In Shanghai,

612
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:03,400
we lost 200,000 brothers.

613
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:05,900
These wounds are nothing.

614
00:32:06,360 --> 00:32:08,440
But after all these years of civil war,

615
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:09,680
you cut me,

616
00:32:10,080 --> 00:32:11,280
and I shoot you.

617
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:14,040
How many of my men have you killed?

618
00:32:14,040 --> 00:32:15,320
How many of yours have I killed?

619
00:32:15,320 --> 00:32:16,320
So many have died,

620
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:18,960
and it's all just Chinese killing Chinese.

621
00:32:19,440 --> 00:32:20,400
Now,

622
00:32:20,720 --> 00:32:22,650
the Japs are right at our doorstep.

623
00:32:23,280 --> 00:32:25,740
Our country is ruined, our homes destroyed.

624
00:32:26,120 --> 00:32:27,450
I'm not afraid of death,

625
00:32:27,640 --> 00:32:30,300
but I am afraid of dying at the hands of a Chinese.

626
00:33:23,880 --> 00:33:26,800
Li Youyu, this is yours.

627
00:33:28,960 --> 00:33:31,720
Zhang Chunhe, this is yours.

628
00:33:32,960 --> 00:33:35,880
Tian Xufeng, this is yours.

629
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:42,120
Zhang Zhongkui, this is yours.

630
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:47,200
Yu Chunwa, this is yours.

631
00:34:19,639 --> 00:34:20,770
My revenge is taken.

632
00:34:23,159 --> 00:34:24,620
But you and your brothers,

633
00:34:25,960 --> 00:34:27,159
none of you can leave.

634
00:34:28,239 --> 00:34:30,570
You must take the place of my dead brothers

635
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:32,360
and go kill the Japs.

636
00:34:38,360 --> 00:34:39,159
Okay.

637
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:41,860
I want to make a phone call.

638
00:34:42,480 --> 00:34:42,960
Okay.

639
00:34:46,080 --> 00:34:47,280
Deputy Corps Commander Liao,

640
00:34:47,280 --> 00:34:48,080
my suggestion

641
00:34:48,159 --> 00:34:49,480
is still to besiege the enemy to strike their reinforcements.

642
00:34:49,480 --> 00:34:50,199
What if the enemy

643
00:34:50,199 --> 00:34:51,560
cuts off our retreat?

644
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:53,610
Report, Chief of Staff.

645
00:34:53,679 --> 00:34:55,120
It's a call from Commander Pang

646
00:34:55,120 --> 00:34:56,840
of the 231st Regiment, 39th Division, 40th Corps.

647
00:34:56,840 --> 00:34:57,770
Commander Pang.

648
00:34:57,800 --> 00:34:58,520
Yes.

649
00:34:59,120 --> 00:34:59,980
Pang Zhonghao.

650
00:35:14,480 --> 00:35:15,320
I'm Lu Yun.

651
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:16,520
Lu Yun,

652
00:35:16,680 --> 00:35:17,480
it's me.

653
00:35:22,760 --> 00:35:23,520
What's up?

654
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:25,160
I'm going to the battlefield.

655
00:35:25,160 --> 00:35:26,020
What happened?

656
00:35:26,320 --> 00:35:27,120
Why?

657
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:28,160
Didn't we say

658
00:35:28,160 --> 00:35:30,080
you'd go to Wuhan to find your family?

659
00:35:30,080 --> 00:35:31,140
I broke my promise.

660
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:32,860
I just want to tell you,

661
00:35:33,640 --> 00:35:35,120
remember what you said.

662
00:35:35,760 --> 00:35:36,890
These past few days,

663
00:35:37,720 --> 00:35:39,450
I've been thinking about this.

664
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:42,020
When we were young,

665
00:35:42,240 --> 00:35:43,920
we always thought we could change history.

666
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:44,800
But actually,

667
00:35:45,240 --> 00:35:46,700
we merely endure history.

668
00:35:48,080 --> 00:35:49,000
You were right.

669
00:35:50,040 --> 00:35:51,370
What is the big picture?

670
00:35:51,520 --> 00:35:53,520
Conscience is the biggest picture.

671
00:35:54,400 --> 00:35:54,920
The documents you wanted,

672
00:35:54,920 --> 00:35:56,450
I've prepared them for you.

673
00:35:56,520 --> 00:35:57,580
Come over tonight,

674
00:35:58,040 --> 00:35:59,280
take these documents,

675
00:35:59,280 --> 00:36:00,600
go to the Ministry of Military Affairs in Wuhan,

676
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:02,120
and clear the names of those 6,000 brothers.

677
00:36:02,120 --> 00:36:03,580
Thank you, old classmate.

678
00:36:03,760 --> 00:36:05,560
But I've already made my decision.

679
00:36:05,560 --> 00:36:06,840
I'm going with Pang Zhonghao of the Northwest Army

680
00:36:06,840 --> 00:36:08,370
to fight the Japs together.

681
00:36:09,120 --> 00:36:09,960
Zhang Yunkui.

682
00:36:10,520 --> 00:36:11,600
What happened?

683
00:36:12,520 --> 00:36:13,400
Can you say?

684
00:36:24,640 --> 00:36:25,320
Okay.

685
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:26,880
I understand.

686
00:36:27,520 --> 00:36:29,120
You suffered more than I did.

687
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:30,620
If we switched places,

688
00:36:31,200 --> 00:36:32,730
I wouldn't be as good as you.

689
00:36:32,840 --> 00:36:34,370
You go to your battlefield.

690
00:36:34,840 --> 00:36:36,560
I'll send all the information,

691
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:37,160
in secret,

692
00:36:37,160 --> 00:36:39,890
to Mr. Huang in the Ministry of Military Affairs.

693
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,320
He is our team leader

694
00:36:41,800 --> 00:36:44,330
and will definitely help you get things done.

695
00:36:59,640 --> 00:37:00,320
Commander.

696
00:37:00,720 --> 00:37:01,380
Commander.

697
00:37:01,560 --> 00:37:02,520
Reporting to the commander.

698
00:37:02,520 --> 00:37:03,040
Speak.

699
00:37:03,160 --> 00:37:04,520
Our left flank has suffered heavy losses.

700
00:37:04,520 --> 00:37:06,240
Almost all our brothers on the front line are dead.

701
00:37:06,240 --> 00:37:07,640
The Japanese army is very likely to

702
00:37:07,640 --> 00:37:09,770
break through our defense line there.

703
00:37:10,920 --> 00:37:11,760
Follow me.

704
00:37:11,920 --> 00:37:12,720
Yes, sir.

705
00:37:21,080 --> 00:37:21,740
Commander.

706
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:22,360
Commander.

707
00:37:22,360 --> 00:37:22,960
What's wrong?

708
00:37:22,960 --> 00:37:23,880
The first and second battalions,

709
00:37:23,880 --> 00:37:24,520
added together now,

710
00:37:24,520 --> 00:37:26,240
can't even make up two platoons.

711
00:37:26,240 --> 00:37:27,240
The enemy's tanks

712
00:37:27,360 --> 00:37:28,760
are causing too many casualties.

713
00:37:28,760 --> 00:37:29,760
What should we do?

714
00:37:31,600 --> 00:37:33,240
Collect grenades.

715
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:36,040
Third platoon, go up and draw their fire.

716
00:37:36,040 --> 00:37:38,360
Yes, sir. Hurry.

717
00:39:54,520 --> 00:39:55,440
Move out.

718
00:40:00,880 --> 00:40:02,320
Cover.

719
00:40:03,280 --> 00:40:04,400
Cover.

720
00:40:38,760 --> 00:40:44,880
Sister wants to hold brother's hand.

721
00:40:46,240 --> 00:40:51,920
Brother wants to kiss sister's mouth.

722
00:40:52,840 --> 00:40:58,640
Holding hands and kissing mouths.

723
00:40:59,920 --> 00:41:04,840
The two of us walk into the corner.

724
00:41:05,560 --> 00:41:06,840
Missing your wife?

725
00:41:07,120 --> 00:41:07,960
Yes.

726
00:41:10,440 --> 00:41:11,360
Don't you?

727
00:41:12,880 --> 00:41:13,520
Yes.

728
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:15,530
They should be in Wuhan.

729
00:41:18,480 --> 00:41:19,360
My son

730
00:41:20,480 --> 00:41:22,940
should have been born at the end of last year.

731
00:41:23,120 --> 00:41:24,240
In a blink of an eye,

732
00:41:24,880 --> 00:41:26,540
it's been over a hundred days.

733
00:41:28,080 --> 00:41:28,880
Actually, I don't even know

734
00:41:28,880 --> 00:41:30,080
if it's a boy or a girl.

735
00:41:30,080 --> 00:41:31,880
But I've already picked out names for them.

736
00:41:31,880 --> 00:41:32,760
What are they?

737
00:41:34,600 --> 00:41:36,060
A boy would be Zhang Bucuo.

738
00:41:36,760 --> 00:41:38,200
A girl would be Zhang Keyi.

739
00:41:38,200 --> 00:41:38,860
Zhang Keyi.

740
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:39,320
Right.

741
00:41:39,640 --> 00:41:40,560
Not bad.

742
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:43,160
Not bad.

743
00:41:44,960 --> 00:41:46,760
What do you mean, 'not bad'?

744
00:41:47,520 --> 00:41:48,980
I don't have the final say.

745
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:50,970
My father makes the decisions.

746
00:41:52,360 --> 00:41:53,200
Anyway,

747
00:41:53,320 --> 00:41:55,250
we can use them as nicknames later.

748
00:41:55,360 --> 00:41:56,220
That works too.

749
00:41:56,480 --> 00:41:57,000
It works.

750
00:41:57,000 --> 00:41:57,600
It works.

751
00:42:01,040 --> 00:42:01,900
What about you?

752
00:42:02,280 --> 00:42:04,140
Your hometown is Yulin, Shaanxi.

753
00:42:04,360 --> 00:42:05,720
Is everyone in your family doing well?

754
00:42:05,720 --> 00:42:07,320
In the countryside of Suide.

755
00:42:09,360 --> 00:42:11,160
My wife is taking care of two kids

756
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:13,200
at home.

757
00:42:13,400 --> 00:42:14,530
And your old mother?

758
00:42:15,200 --> 00:42:16,880
My mother's eyes are bad.

759
00:42:18,320 --> 00:42:19,120
She can't see.

760
00:42:24,080 --> 00:42:24,920
Zhang Yunkui.

761
00:42:26,200 --> 00:42:27,120
You said

762
00:42:28,400 --> 00:42:31,400
you were afraid of dying at the hands of Chinese people.

763
00:42:31,400 --> 00:42:32,360
I'm afraid too.

764
00:42:39,200 --> 00:42:41,600
It's left over from the Central Plains War.

765
00:42:42,040 --> 00:42:42,760
Kaifeng.

766
00:42:43,320 --> 00:42:43,980
Zhengzhou.

767
00:42:44,600 --> 00:42:45,760
Mamuji.

768
00:42:46,600 --> 00:42:47,330
This is good.

769
00:42:47,520 --> 00:42:49,850
I got this fighting the Japs at Xifengkou.

770
00:42:49,880 --> 00:42:51,040
When fighting the Japs,

771
00:42:51,040 --> 00:42:53,300
I chipped the blades of two broadswords.

772
00:42:55,440 --> 00:42:57,300
As long as it's fighting the Japs,

773
00:42:57,560 --> 00:42:58,760
it's worth dying for.

774
00:43:00,360 --> 00:43:01,220
Tai'erzhuang.

775
00:43:02,760 --> 00:43:04,080
This is a great place.
